description.value: Egyptian blue scarab, back rubbed, with outline of clypeus and prothorax just marked. and elytra division faintly visible. Legs undercut, and longitudinally pierced under projecting elements of carapace.. Device represents two animals, deeply incised, arranged one above the other: couchant lion in upper field,  grazing deer in lower field, similar to Archaic Greek gems, with single oval line incised round edge.Style of animals is similar to other Naukratite scarabs. Blue paste hard, grainy in texture.
